│ "1. Understanding the Issue: The crash occurs in `canonicalizeICmpBool()`   │
│ function when processing an icmp instruction with predicate `ICMP_NE`       │
│ comparing a vector of i1 values against `zeroinitializer`. The function     │
│ assumes that when comparing boolean vectors against constants, the constant │
│ must be either all-zeros (`m_Zero()`) or all-ones (`m_One()`), but for      │
│ scalable vectors like `<vscale x 8 x i1> zeroinitializer`, the pattern      │
│ matching fails to recognize it as a zero constant, causing the code to fall │
